<br>
It was quite clearly stated at the end of the first war in the gulf that the burden of proof was on saddam.  At one point in time, he has weapons of mass destruction.  We all know this and agree on it.  If you don't you're a moron, even Saddam doesn't deny this.  Now, the natural assumption unless there is evidence to the contrary is that he still does.  If there is no evidence that anything has changed, we must believe nothing has.<br>
<br>
Now on another note, you say that lobbing 3000 cruise missiles isn't going to make things better.  Well, I disagree.  Right now the war of Iraqi independence is about to be fought.  It will be a revolution during which an evil dictator will be removed from power and replaced with a regime that listens to the voice of the people.<br>
<br>
You could have made the same absurd argument about the American revolution.  Sure the Americans were being oppressed by the English, but fighting a war would get people killed.  What good would that do?  Well, many Americans feel that that war did a great deal of good.  I certainly do.<br>
